Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Candente, Credicorp, Southern Copper

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-09-22T20:48:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/peru-stocks-buenaventura-candente-credicorp-southern-copper.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell for a fourth session, losing
4.6 percent to 19,011.88. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped
7.2 percent to 2,424.92.  Industrial and banking shares plummeted after U.S. stocks
and commodities slumped, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-
based brokerage Coril SAB.  Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based
steelmaker, fell 9.1 percent to 2.20 soles.  Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1
PE), Peru’s largest foodstuff maker, dropped 6.8 percent to 5.45
soles. Edegel SA (EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian unit of  Spain ’s
Endesa SA, declined 5.2 percent to 1.47 soles.  Intergroup
Financial Services Corp. (IFS)  , the owner of Peru’s fourth-
largest bank, Interbank, fell 5.2 percent to $23.70.  Credicorp
Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services holding
company, slid 5.2 percent to $95.  Copper and gold miners fell after the metals declined in
New York and  London .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, plunged 13 percent to $42.20, its
biggest one-day drop since Dec. 18, 2008.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO) 
, Peru’s biggest copper producer, declined 9.9 percent
to $25.40.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold
exploration company, dropped 8.2 percent to $2.80.  Candente
Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration company, fell for
a fourth session, losing 8.2 percent to $1.01.  Alturas Minerals
Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian gold and copper exploration company,
slid 7.7 percent to 12 cents, a three-month low.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  